quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  20,109,"That Day, no intercession will benefit except [that of] one to whom the Most Merciful has given permission and has accepted his word."
  20,110,"He [i.e., Allāh] knows what is [presently] before them and what will be after them,{1} but they do not encompass it [i.e., what He knows] in knowledge.",footnotes:1:[See footnote to 2:255.]
  20,111,"And [all] faces will be humbled before the Ever-Living, the Self-Sustaining.{1} And he will have failed who carries injustice.{2}",footnotes:1:[See footnotes],footnotes:2:[to 2:255.]
  21,85,"And [mention] Ishmael and Idrees and Dhul-Kifl; all were of the patient."
  21,86,"And We admitted them into Our mercy. Indeed, they were of the righteous."
  21,87,"And [mention] the man of the fish [i.e., Jonah], when he went off in anger{1} and thought that We would not decree [anything] upon him.{2} And he called out within the darknesses,{3} "There is no deity except You; exalted are You. Indeed, I have been of the wrongdoers."",footnotes:1:[At the disbelief of his people.],footnotes:2:[Or \"would not restrict him\" in the belly of the fish.],footnotes:3:[That of the night, of the sea, and of the fish's interior.]
  22,61,"That{1} is because Allāh causes the night to enter the day and causes the day to enter the night and because Allāh is Hearing and Seeing.",footnotes:1:[i.e., Allāh's capability to give assistance or victory to the oppressed.]
  22,62,"That is because Allāh is the True Reality, and that which they call upon other than Him is falsehood, and because Allāh is the Most High, the Grand."
  22,63,"Do you not see that Allāh has sent down rain from the sky and the earth becomes green? Indeed, Allāh is Subtle{1} and Aware.{2}",footnotes:1:[Refer to footnote of 6:103.],footnotes:2:[Of His creation and of the needs of His creatures.]
  23,37,"It [i.e., life] is not but our worldly life - we die and live, but we will not be resurrected."
  23,38,"He is not but a man who has invented a lie about Allāh, and we will not believe him."
  23,39,"He said, "
  24,19,"Indeed, those who like that immorality{1} should be spread [or publicized] among those who have believed will have a painful punishment in this world and the Hereafter. And Allāh knows{2} and you do not know.",footnotes:1:[Specifically, unlawful sexual relations.],footnotes:2:[The hidden aspects of all things:  what is beneficial and what is harmful.]
  24,20,"And if it had not been for the favor of Allāh upon you and His mercy...{1} and because Allāh is Kind and Merciful.",footnotes:1:[See footnote to verse 10.]
  24,21,"O you who have believed, do not follow the footsteps of Satan. And whoever follows the footsteps of Satan - indeed, he enjoins immorality and wrongdoing. And if not for the favor of Allāh upon you and His mercy, not one of you would have been pure, ever, but Allāh purifies whom He wills, and Allāh is Hearing and Knowing."
